    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "2 Timothy",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 4,
        "summary": "Paul gives a solemn charge to preach the gospel in a day of apostasy\u2014Paul and all Saints are assured of exaltation.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "I charge thee therefore before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, who shall judge the quick and the dead at his appearing and his kingdom;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Preach the word; be instant in season, out of season; reprove, rebuke, exhort with all longsuffering and doctrine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Missionary Work; Preaching.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a02\u00a0Tim. 4:2 \u2026 be instant in season, those who are out of season\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0urgent, earnest.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening; Reproof.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the time will come when they will not endure sound doctrine; but after their own lusts shall they heap to themselves teachers, having itching ears;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Tim. 3:1; Hel. 13:28 (26\u201330).",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 1:10.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lust.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 90
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Prophets; Teacher.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall turn away their ears from the truth, and shall be turned unto fables.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Truth.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But watch thou in all things, endure afflictions, do the work of an evangelist, make full proof of thy ministry.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Watch.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 21:8; Eph. 4:11 (11\u201314).",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0fulfill your ministry.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I am now ready to be offered, and the time of my departure is at hand.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have fought a good fight, I have finished my course, I have kept the faith:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contentment.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dedication.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Henceforth there is laid up for me a crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous judge, shall give me at that day: and not to me only, but unto all them also that love his appearing.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Exaltation; Reward.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Do thy diligence to come shortly unto me:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For Demas hath forsaken me, having loved this present world, and is departed unto Thessalonica; Crescens to Galatia, Titus unto Dalmatia.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 4:14; Philem. 1:24.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worldliness.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Only Luke is with me. Take Mark, and bring him with thee: for he is profitable to me for the ministry.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 1:1.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 15:37 (37\u201339); Col. 4:10.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Tychicus have I sent to Ephesus.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The cloak that I left at Troas with Carpus, when thou comest, bring with thee, and the books, but especially the parchments.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 1:1 (1\u20134); 1\u00a0Ne. 13:26 (24\u201326).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Alexander the coppersmith did me much evil: the Lord reward him according to his works:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 64:11.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Of whom be thou ware also; for he hath greatly withstood our words.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0opposed, resisted.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "At my first answer no man stood with me, but all men forsook me: I pray God that it may not be laid to their charge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0defense.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 7:60 (59\u201360); 3\u00a0Ne. 12:44.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Notwithstanding the Lord stood with me, and strengthened me; that by me the preaching might be fully known, and that all the Gentiles might hear: and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 14:18.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 116
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord shall deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me unto his heavenly kingdom: to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0save, rescue.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Salute Prisca and Aquila, and the household of Onesiphorus.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Erastus abode at Corinth: but Trophimus have I left at Miletum sick.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Do thy diligence to come before winter. Eubulus greeteth thee, and Pudens, and Linus, and Claudia, and all the brethren.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord Jesus Christ be with thy spirit. Grace be with you. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Lord.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}